					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table5">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table6">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=531995">Shar Vahl</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Shar Vahl Bard Drum Quest</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Shar Vahl Bard Drum Quest</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=533012"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Teleporting Chronotrigger</a> | 
		                        12/13/2001 2:45:46 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">This is a relativley easy quest which is good for bards in order to get their percussion instruments. After completeting your citizenship quest Head to Gherik in the Pottery shop and hand him your slate. He will mention that he needs 3 scorpion shells, which can be found in newbie pit in Shar Vahl. After gathering the 3 scorpion shells(which BTW are no drop) head back to Gherik and make sure you have 2 open inv slots because after turning in Shells he will hand you a Claymixing Bowl and a Reusable Bowl sketch and he Tells you next instructions which is to gather 4 Grimling Femur's and grind them in the claymixing bowl.  Once again the femur's are drops obviously off the grimling skeles found in newbie pit. After you have gathered the femur bones you must then combine them in the bowl and you will acquire a dust of some sort.  Put the dust back in the bowl and then get some Xakra bile found off worms roaming once again in newbie pit. Once you have acquired the bile you must then combine the Grinded bones with the bile and a flask of water (store brought) to make what I think they call glowing bile clay.  After you have done that I suggest that at this time you might wanna try to practice your pottery skill seeing you will need to use them in awhile.  Anyways head back to the pottery shop grab a pottery wheel and cross your fingers....LOL you will need the luck. Combine the clay with the sketch Gherik gave you and a flask of water ( once again store brought ).  LOL X your fingers...lol and if you are successful you will make a unfired bowl now hand Gherik the unfired bowl and he will give you more instructions. I am at this point in which you want to go to Broker Fahaar which is a vendor in the alley before you get to the main castle. Hand him your citizenship slate and the rest is but a fog to me anyone wanting to clear the rest up TAKE IT AWAY!!!!!!<BR>
<BR>
Teleporting Chronotrigger 40 Erudite wizzie<BR>
Howlingpaws 6 Vah Shir Bard<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
