	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay.  Here's some more notes to this quest.  <BR>
<BR>
After you collect the scorpion shells and such you do this :<BR>
Gherik wants you to collect four grimling bones (which drops off of grimling skeletons in the pit below the city) and he wants you to combine them in the claymixing bowl.  This requires NO skill, so don't worry.  You'll wind up with Grimling Powder.  <BR>
<BR>
Put the Grimling Powder in the claymixing bowl with a water flask and a xakra worm bile (drops uncommonly off of xakra worms down in pit below city) combine them (this again takes NO skills) you'll end up with some clay (forgot name of it) Spin the sketch that Gherik gives you , the clay, and a water flask to create an unfired bowl.  Return the unfired bowl to Gherik.<BR>
<BR>
Fire the bowl in a kiln with water flask and a quality firing sheet.  Get you skills of pottery up in the 20's b4 you do this though.  It helps a lot , trust me.  Then you'll get a Jharin bowl (sp?) .  Head to Broker Fahaar who is near the palace.  (Going down the palace steps and walking into the long corridor that stretches from left to right and has merchants on each side, go left and you'll see either 2 or 3 merchants, 1 of them is Broker Fahaar.) Show him the acrylia slate and he will give you a bag to put 4 young rockhopper hides in.  <BR>
<BR>
Go down in the pit and kill young rockhoppers for their hides.  They drop them uncommonly and look like needle clawed hoppers but are around lvl 4 or 5 and are a tanish color.  Once you have 4 HIDES (not skins) return with them in the bag to the Broker.  He gives you a leather cord, a stretched rockhopper hide, and an initiate's cloak (Wow! what a deal!) Then return the bowl, cloak, stretched hide, and leather cord to Gherik.  He'll give you a buckler, a cloak, and a drum.  <BR>
<BR>
Good luck guys! =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
